{"id": "cbse-12-sci-electromagnetic-waves-electromagnetic-waves-mcq-24861", "legacy_id": "aae15588a6ee75f3", "curriculum": "cbse", "grade": "12", "sku": "cbse12-science", "subject": "physics", "chapter_id": "electromagnetic-waves", "topic": "electromagnetic-waves", "concept": "electromagnetic-waves", "graph_refs": ["kg:cbse:12:physics:electromagnetic-waves:concept:core-concepts"], "source_refs": ["55(B)-S Physics.pdf"], "question_type": "mcq_single", "question": "When an electron of hydrogen atom jumps from a ground state energy level to higher energy level, it absorbs energy and is excited. It can remain in this state for a maximum time j 10–7s. When de-excited, the electron returns back and the same amount of energy is radiated in the form of a photon. The difference of energies of two energy levels (Ef – Ei) is the energy of this photon. Depending upon the two levels involved in transition, the spectral lines are grouped in five series of hydrogen line emission spectrum. These are named as Lyman (nf = 1), Balmer (nf = 2), Paschen (nf = 3), Brackett (nf = 4) and Pfund (nf = 5) series. The values of energy of the electron in the nth level of hydrogen atom and of hydrogen-like atom are 2 –13.6 n eV and 2 –13.6 n Z2 eV respectively. Here Z is number of protons in the nucleus of hydrogen-like atom. (i) Which one of the following hydrogen spectral series lie in visible region ? 1", "options": ["Lyman", "Balmer", "Pfund", "Lyman"], "answer": "Lyman", "answer_index": 0, "explanation": "The correct response is: Lyman. This item was imported from 55(B)-S Physics.pdf with legacy provenance.", "interesting_fact": "", "difficulty": 2, "bloom": "remember", "competency_band": "conceptual", "marks": 1, "misconception_tested": "", "learning_objective": "Master electromagnetic waves", "learning_outcome": "Master electromagnetic waves", "game_skills": ["mcq"], "game_compat": ["practice", "mock"], "forbidden_modes": [], "source": "legacy_import", "generator": "legacy_import", "generator_version": "1.0.0", "validator_version": "1.0.0", "confidence_score": 0.75, "verified": false, "status": "validated", "version": 1, "metadata": {"track": null, "section": null, "passage_context": null, "has_diagram": false, "delivery_mode": "mcq"}}
